WorkItem.Description:
I think de YUI javascript minimizer does not user an InvariantCulture for formatting. Because my local culture is Dutch, al my javascript numbers get converter from decimal-point to decimal-comma's. Which gives a totaly different meaning to my code.

For example:

if( a > 0.05 )
becomes
if(a>0,05)

now suddenly the test is always true, because a comma is a command seperator. And 5 is always true.
